reviews.headline: I would buy this product again
reviews.comments: Love Bare Minerals & finally picked the perfect match to my skin tone

reviews.headline: I would not buy this product again
reviews.comments: I had bought this thinking it was supposed to be kind on my lines and creases.  It in fact made them appear worse.  Too dry also.  Will be returning.

reviews.headline: Not sure.
reviews.comments: Not enough coverage.

reviews.headline: Beautiful Finish
reviews.comments: Bare Minerals matte finish foundation goes in easy , covers beautifully but not heavy at all. I have mature skin but in no way does it cake up or look heavy

reviews.headline: I wold but this product again.
reviews.comments: It feels really light on my skin. Love the tone and great product.

reviews.headline: This Formula is horrible
reviews.comments: I used to love this foundation and then they changed the formula.  Now is thick and cakey.  I've been using it for years and now I have to find another foundation that won't break me out.

reviews.headline: Not worth the hassle
reviews.comments: This has got to be the WORST foundation. I have dry skin and was looking for a 24 hour foundation that didn't break me out. This foundation separates in the first hours of wear. I regret ever buying this.

reviews.headline: Bring Back the Old BarePro Formula
reviews.comments: I miss the old formula just as so many others have stated in the comments. The old formula was buildable coverage and so breathable and smooth on the skin. This formula is thick and heavy, not buildable coverage (too full coverage imo), very drying on the skin, and emphasizes pores and texture. I really hope bareMinerals sees the feedback and stops making so many changes to their core skus. This foundation was my favorite but I'll be moving on from it sadly.

reviews.headline: Nope.
reviews.comments: I was excited for a cleaner foundation with SPF. While this is a perfeft match for my skin tone (which seems so hard to find), this is streaky spotty, and settles into my pores immediately. I have tried priners, powders, etc. it also wears off so easily and transfers to everything. Not a fan and would not recommend. I will be returning this because there is no way I can stick it out and finish the bottle. It is awful.

reviews.headline: Drying
reviews.comments: Color was a perfect match and it initially went on great. I thought I was going to love it over the previous version but unfortunately not. Within a couple hours it looked horrible. It was particularly dry and patchy looking around my mouth. I, unfortunately had to switch brands for the first time  in over 10 years.

reviews.headline: Use caution
reviews.comments: This product has changed from the company who previously owned it. I find it to be more greasy & heavy on my skin.  If a drop gets on my clothing it doesn't come out. Anything touched after using it will leave the product stain on everything. Disappointing!

reviews.headline: ORANGE Orange Orange and MORE ORANGE
reviews.comments: Bare Minerals, PLEASE HIRE A COMPETENT COLORIST, someone who knows how to mix color, someone with experience. All of your shades in the medium-light to fair range are tinted ORANGE. You've got a warm orange, a cool orange, a neutral orange, a light orange, a fair orange, a medium orange and a dark orange. What happened to all the beautiful BEIGE tones, the tones that match our skin tones? It's impossible to choose a color online and no easier inside the store. Inside the store, you'll find a long row of Bare Minerals frosty glass bottles, most of which look like they contain ORANGE SHERBERT ice cream. Please, Bare Minerals, NEUTRALIZE THE ORANGE.

reviews.headline: Bring back the Performance 24hr wear foundation
reviews.comments: I tried this foundation simply because Bareminerals no longer carries the 24hr Performance wear line of foundation. All the is Matte formula did was "separate" on my face looking like a cheap make up job.

reviews.headline: This is my favorite foundation!!
reviews.comments: I ran out of this one and went to Ulta and they didn't have this color and gave me a different one and I didn't like it. So I ordered on line!

reviews.headline: Love it
reviews.comments: Idk why all the hate! I love this. I've tried many many different matte full coverage foundations and this is the one.

reviews.headline: Bring back Latte 24
reviews.comments: No I would not ! It is supposed to replace my original color

reviews.headline: I only comment when it's necessary
reviews.comments: The old formula of this foundation was one of my favorites, this new formula is awful. Why fix it if it's not broken!

reviews.headline: PLEASE BRING BACK THE OLD FORMULA
reviews.comments: Please bring back the old formula! This is far FAR inferior!

reviews.headline: Bring back the old formula!!!
reviews.comments: This stuff works okay full coverage. However the previous formula was amazing and since it has been discontinued I have never been able to find a shade that perfeftly matches my skin. Such a shame.

reviews.headline: Great lightweight full coverage foundation
reviews.comments: BAREPRO 24HR has a great range of colors/tones. It's lightweight and blends easily. I use 3 drops on a brush and it provides a very natural looking full coverage.

faceoff_positive.comments: I am completely shocked by how amazing this foundation is.  I've been a EL Double Wear user for probably 20 years because I love a full coverage, transfer-proof foundation.  However, the last few years, as I've entered my 40's my skin has become unquenchably dry.  No matter how much I exfoliated, moisturized and primed, the Double Wear was just sucking the life out of my skin.  I've tried just about everything that's come to market in hopes of finding  a full coverage foundation that is long-lasting, transfer proof, comfortable to wear and non-drying, only to return them all and give up hope.  This foundation fits the bill!  It is a solid medium to full coverage and buildable without looking cakey.  It covers my dime-sized patch of hormonal cheek melasma and dark undereye circles without the need for additional concealer.  It's a thin, somewhat runny consistency so I was totally surprised at how pigmented it was!  Not to mention, this stuff does not budge all day, and it doesn't make me look like I'm 10 years older than I am. My face does not feel tight, dry, oily or heavy wearing this.   Goes smoothly over dry areas, doesn't make me oily in the t-zone, and wears like iron but feels absolutely weightless.  The finish is definitely matte, but it's a natural matte as opposed to a super matte like EL DW or Kat Von D.    For reference, I am light to barely medium, very yellow undertones and the shade Golden Nude is an absolute perfect match (NC20-25). I cannot even express how happy I am to have finally found my forever foundation.
faceoff_positive.headline: Amazing foundation

faceoff_negative.comments: I was having problems with all the drug store foundations. They weren't giving me the coverage I needed and they'd just smear right off if I barley touched my face. So, I went on a search for a good high end foundation that I knew would be great quality. When I went to Ulta and tried several different brands and shades I knew this one would give me the coverage I was looking for. Once I started using it, I fell in love with the way it looked. It applies full coverage if you put on two coats. It is a matte finish and lasts all day. I wouldn't say it's "sweat or waterproof" because after working out it didn't look that great. However, I just loved everything about it, it was perfect. Then, I started to break out on my chin and lower cheek area. I could not figure out what was causing it. I even changed my face wash and my face moisturizer to see if that was it. But, my face began to clear up because I'm not a person to wear makeup each day. I hadn't worn makeup for nearly a week. I put applied this foundation and by the end of the day, after removing it, two new blemishes had appeared on my face. I think this foundation is great, but it literally sticks to your skin and you gotta work to get it all off. I wish this wouldn't of broke me out because I love it.
faceoff_negative.headline: Love the product, but there's an aftershock
